\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \'93Much quicker and easier, really cuts out the fat.\'94\'93Compared to Wae, working in Bullhorn is like doing your job twice. In Wae, it\'92s just click click and done, much better use of my time.\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Suggestions/Input\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls131\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Participants mentioned a current issue with the Bullhorn system where there\'92s difficulty editing qualifications on the fly, and cautioned us to avoid this issue in Wae.\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls131\ilvl1\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The example they gave is that some jobs were set to require a vaccination, but now time has passed and our customer no longer requires it. Candidates that don\'92t have the vaccination would not be able to apply since the job was originally entered with that requirement.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls131\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Participants also mentioned that entering jobs directly into indeed gives them a lot more control and they can be much more specific than what they can do in Bullhorn. They think any future solution should meet what indeed offers in general.\
\ls131\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Participants mentioned certain larger employers that currently create a spreadsheet in an email of their needs and then just CC all the staffing agencies. In these cases, it\'92s difficult to expect them to download Wae and enter it all in the app and sacrifice what they\'92re getting by sending it to multiple agencies.\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls131\ilvl1\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 A possible partial-fix would be to allow CS-admins batch-input of jobs by importing the spreadsheet. then we would just have to be sure we are aware of the edge cases like if some other agencies fills the remaining positions, we would have to remove the openings before a candidate signs up.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa321\partightenfactor0

